Arrays - numerical indexes must have sequential order, starting from zero.

a = new Array
a.resize(2) - method to set size of array
a[0] = 1
a[1] = "123"
a[] = "hello" // size of array will be 3
a[4] = "world" // must be ignored; warning will be written to log
a.erase(index) - method to remove one element, numerical indexes must save sequential order after removing element
a.insert(index, value) - method to insert one element, numerical indexes must save sequential order after removing element
a.length - read-only property with count of elements      

String extended support
s.trim
s.ltrim
s.rtrim
s.length
s.replace
s.insert
s.erase
s.find
s.find_first_of
s.find_last_of
s.substr
regular expressions

Hashtables
a = new Hashtable
a["key"] = "value" // any UniVar can be key or value
a.removeKey("key") - method to remove something from hashtable
a.keyExists("key") - method to check if key exists
a.length - read-only property with count of elements      
foreach (pair in a)	// foreach for traversal of hashtable
{
	print pair.key
	print pair.value
}


Empty object
a = new Object
a.prop1 = 1
a.prop2 = 2

